text: Nordingrå is a locality in Kramfors Municipality in Västernorrland County in Sweden. In 2010, 306 people lived there. It is also a parish of about 50 villages, with about 1,500 people living there. Nordingrå is a part of the Höga Kusten (High Coast) World Heritage Site. == Notable people == * Arne Åhman (1925–2022), athlete == References == Category:Settlements in Vasternorrland County
title: Nordingrå
